Class Brush.HTMLScriptRegExp

java.lang.Object
  syntaxhighlighter.Brush.HTMLScriptRegExp
Enclosing class:
Brush
public static class Brush.HTMLScriptRegExp
extends java.lang.Object

Regular expression for HTML script. This will be used to determine if the language was implanted into the HTML using left and right. e.g. left is "", if there is any content start with "", the content in between these two will be parsed by using this brush.

getpattern

public java.util.regex.Pattern getpattern()
Get the pattern of this HTML script RegExp. Itis a combination of left and right tag and some pattern to match the in-between content. Group 1 is the left tag, group 2 is the inner content, group 3 is the right tag.

Returns:
the pattern with flags: CASE_INSENSITIVE and DOTALL
